{
  "texts": [
    "There are a number of variants of data-adaptive mechanism design that leverage PTR-like ideas, but do not suffer from the aforementioned limitations.",
    "They are less widely applicable than the vanilla (distance-testbased) PTR, but are computationally efficient when they qualify.",
    "These approaches include privately bounding local sensitivity, which avoids the 'propose' step of PTR, and privately testing the stability margin",
    "[NO_PRINTED_FORM], which avoids the part that adds noise, and thus also works for non-numeric queries.",
    "A concise treatment of these methods is given in Vadhan (2017)."
  ]
}